\\ The first program that anyone will write most probably is the Hello World program in C Language. Here's the program

#include <stdio.h>
int main (void)

{
    printf("hello world\n");
}

\\The stdio.h (Standard Input Output Header) is one of the most fundamental header files in C. 
\\It provides functionalities for input and output (I/O) operations such as reading from the keyboard and writing to the console.

\\printf()	Prints formatted output to the console.

int → The function returns an integer value (typically 0 for success).
main → The function's name (the program's starting point).
void → It means that the function takes no arguments.

Here are some of the data Types:
Data Types
int - %i
float - %f
bool - %i
char - %c
string - %s

